 
INTRODUCTION
------------

The code contains one baseline(experiment0) and seven experiments:
experiment0
experiment1
experiment2
experiment3_1
experiment3_2
experiment4
experiment5_1
experiment5_2

Each function prints out the perfomance metrics and other information.
They also plot prediction-recall scatter plots. 

REQUIRED LIBRARIES
------------
* nltk
* pandas
* numpy
* re
* sklearn.utils  shuffle
* sklearn.model_selection KFold
* matplotlib.pyplot
* nltk  word_tokenize
* sklearn.feature_extraction.text CountVectorizer
* sklearn.feature_extraction.text TfidfVectorizer
* sklearn.linear_model LogisticRegression
* statistics mean
* statistics  stdev
* sklearn.metrics  accuracy_score
* sklearn.metrics  precision_score
* sklearn.metrics  recall_score
* sklearn.metrics  precision_recall_fscore_support
* sklearn.metrics  classification_report, confusion_matrix
* nltk.corpus  stopwords
* nltk.stem.porter  PorterStemmer
* nltk.corpus  wordnet 


HOW TO RUN
------------
You can run the file from top to bottom.
You have to uncomment the lines to run the baseline and experiments functions.


EXAMPLE OUTPUT
------------
exp0_errors = experiment0(X,y)
